<section class="shell section prose">
	<h2>Before you start</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Both systems are turned on and off via plugs at the back of the stage.</li>
		<li>Please ensure both are turned off when you finish.</li>
		<li>If you turn the sound off, wait 10 seconds before switching it back on.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Lighting</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>The lights are controlled via foot pedals.</li>
		<li>Please use them to set the right lighting for your booking.</li>
		<li>There are disco and flat modes with a range of colours.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Sound</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>You can connect via Bluetooth using <strong>Music BT</strong> with passcode <strong>0000</strong>.</li>
		<li>Cables can be linked into the headphone sockets in the cabinet and outside.</li>
		<li>There is a radio mic; please switch it off before leaving so the batteries do not drain.</li>
		<li>You can connect mixing desks, instruments and microphones via the external sockets.</li>
		<li>Please keep volumes considerate for neighbours.</li>
	</ul>
</section>
